The '''Delaware North Building''' is a [[mixed-use development]] in [[Buffalo, New York]]. The 12-story, 330,000-square-foot mixed-use building features [[Office#Grading|Class A office space]], a 120-room [[Westin]] hotel, ground level retail, a 7,000-square-foot outdoor courtyard, and an adjacent structured parking ramp. [[Delaware North|Delaware North's]] World Headquarters anchors the building.

==Construction==
The new building replaces the two story Delaware Court building (1917-2014) at the northwest corner of Delaware Avenue and Chippewa Street<ref>{{cite web | url=http://preservationready.org/Buildings/250DelawareAvenue | title=Delaware Court Building | publisher=PSR | date=23 April 2014 | accessdate=2 May 2014}}</ref> and occupies a 1.95 acre site.<ref name="Uniland Info Sheet">{{cite web | url=http://uniland.com/pdf/uploads/Uniland_%20250%20Delaware%20Information%20Sheet.pdf | title=Uniland Info Sheet | publisher=Uniland Development | date=10 October 2014 | accessdate=15 October 2014}}</ref> The new building replicates the iconic curved fa√ßade of the old, using [[terra cotta]] features of the original structure.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://bostonvalley.com/blog/2014/02/26/250-delaware-north/ | title=3D Scanning of 250 Delaware Avenue Preps Project | publisher=Boston Valley Terra Cotta | accessdate=3 May 2014}}</ref> The building features 193,000 sq.ft of class A office space on the sixth through 12th floors, a 116-room hotel occupying 104,000 sq. ft., 18,000 sq.ft. of retail space, and indoor parking for 593 vehicles in a five-level attached parking ramp.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.bizjournals.com/buffalo/news/2014/05/07/uniland-adds-fifth-level-to-new-parking-garage.html | title=Uniland adds fifth level to new parking garage | publisher=Buffalo Business First | date=7 May 2014 | accessdate=7 May 2014}}</ref> The building's 2,600-square-foot lobby features the largest living green wall in Western New York, a 22x21 foot expanse of plants providing beauty, improving indoor air quality, and reducing energy use.{{how|date=June 2017}} The building was designed and constructed to achieve a [[Leadership in Energy and Environmental Design|LEED]]-Silver certification through the U.S. Green Building Council.{{citation needed|date=February 2017}}

==Operations==
The Delaware North Building serves as the new headquarters for namesake company [[Delaware North]], which also operates a 116-room [[Westin Hotels & Resorts|Westin hotel]] and Patina 250 restaurant within the building.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.bizjournals.com/buffalo/news/2013/12/16/unilands-80m-building-incentives.html | title=Uniland incentive package OK'd by ECIDA | publisher=Buffalo Business First | accessdate=2 May 2014}}</ref> Other tenants include [[KeyBank]] offices and retail branch, [[UBS Financial Services]], the Department of Homeland Security, the Cullen Foundation, and Osteopathic Wellness Medicine.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.uniland.com|title=Uniland Development Company|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref>

